# socheli-phone-agent — drives the social apps on a physical Android to POST
# finished Socheli videos. Runs on the same Mac that renders (reads data/runs
# directly), so it needs no API token.

# Numeric lockscreen PIN for unattended auto-unlock (plaintext — keep private).
# Without it, the phone must already be unlocked when a run starts.
# DEVICE_PIN=

# Optional: pin a specific device when several are connected (`adb devices`).
# PHONE_SERIAL=

# Optional: explicit adb path (launchd has a minimal PATH).
# ADB_BIN=/opt/homebrew/bin/adb

# Optional: where on the phone to stage the video before posting. Apps surface
# the newest item in DCIM/Camera first, which is why that's the default.
# MEDIA_DIR=/sdcard/DCIM/Camera

# Optional: repo root override (defaults to three levels up from src/).
# SOCHELI_ROOT=/Users/you/development/Socheli
